article.headline: Nevada 92, UTEP 63
article.story: RENO, Nev. (AP) -- Nick Fazekas had a career-best 32 points and 15 rebounds as Nevada beat UTEP 92-63 Saturday night. Garry Hill-Thomas added 15 and Kirk Snyder 12 for the Wolf Pack (16-7, 10-4 WAC), which improved to 12-0 at home this season. Todd Okeson finished with 10 points for Nevada. Omar Thomas scored 25 and Filiberto Rivera 18 to lead the Miners (18-5, 9-4). UTEP came into the game with a six-game winning streak, but couldn't find an answer for Fazekas, who had 20 points and eight rebounds in the first half. With the score tied at 10 with 15:49 left in the first half, Nevada went on a 15-4 run capped by a pair of Fazekas 3-pointers, putting the Wolf Pack ahead 25-14 with 9:39 remaining. The Miners scored four straight to cut the lead to 25-18, but Nevada put the game away with a 16-4 run to end the first half and an 8-0 burst to open the second. The two runs gave the Wolf Pack a 49-22 lead with 17:22 left in the game, and UTEP got no closer than 21 points the rest of the way. Nevada outrebounded UTEP 50-31, including a 16-8 advantage in offensive rebounds. The Wolf Pack shot 47.8 percent from the field, and held UTEP to 38.5 percent.
